   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>The role of the logged-in user should be <uicontrol>Fund Manager</uicontrol>.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>
         <p>You can deactivate an active <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol> record. If a fund source is marked as inactive, then the  fund source will not be available for projects.<note>Deactivating a global fund source that is already assigned to a project does not change the
assigned fund source data of the project.</note>
         </p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Enterprise Dashboard</uicontrol> is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand the <uicontrol>Fund Management </uicontrol> folder, and then click <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>GLOBAL FUND LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the list page, select the appropriate record to deactivate, and then perform either of the following:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>
                     <p>In the toolbar, click  <uicontrol>Mark Active/Inactive</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol>Mark Inactive</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p>In the toolbar, click <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>, clear  the <uicontrol>Is Active</uicontrol> check box, and then click <uicontrol>Save &amp; Exit</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
            <p>The selected record is marked as inactive.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
